{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform council tax to a 0.48% charge of the current property value",
        "additional_details": "The Fairer Share Campaign has highlighted that a property in Middlesbrough worth \u00a3150,000 (with a tax bill of \u00a31,702) pays over 1% of the value of the house in tax, whilst an \u00a38 million home in Westminster (with a tax bill of \u00a31,560) pays only 0.02%. This creates an unjust disparity.\r\n \r\nThus the Government must replace this structure with a fairer system that reflects property value to ensure everyone in society pays an equal share.",
        "background": "The current council tax system is not sufficiently progressive. To rectify this the Government should impose a blanket council tax rate of 0.48% of a property\u2019s existing value (which is annually evaluated) ensuring a fairer system.",
